00:27:30,400 --> 00:27:31,760
Dr. Gu is a scientist.

546
00:27:31,760 --> 00:27:33,320
He's here for science outreach interviews.

547
00:27:33,320 --> 00:27:34,680
Please don't take a gossipy
or intrusive attitude

548
00:27:34,680 --> 00:27:35,680
with your questions.

549
00:27:35,680 --> 00:27:36,820
Okay?

550
00:27:36,820 --> 00:27:38,240
If you understand things so well,

551
00:27:38,240 --> 00:27:39,880
you should take this seat.

552
00:27:40,680 --> 00:27:42,080
Come on.

553
00:27:42,080 --> 00:27:43,440
You can be the host.

554
00:27:52,040 --> 00:27:53,440
We stop filming. Let's go.

555
00:28:01,640 --> 00:28:02,752
Dr. Gu.

556
00:28:04,200 --> 00:28:05,320
Dr. Gu.

557
00:28:24,320 --> 00:28:26,600
Sir, as usual at eight tomorrow morning.

558
00:28:26,600 --> 00:28:28,360
At the entrance of the building.
You worked hard today.

559
00:28:28,360 --> 00:28:29,640
Alright, Miss Han.

560
00:28:29,640 --> 00:28:30,752
Goodbye.

561
00:28:34,560 --> 00:28:35,640
Let's have dinner together.

562
00:28:37,880 --> 00:28:39,880
Not today, too tired.

563
00:28:39,880 --> 00:28:41,720
I have your interview manuscript
to check later.

564
00:28:47,000 --> 00:28:48,080
What's wrong?

565
00:28:48,080 --> 00:28:49,120
Follow me.

566
00:28:54,624 --> 00:28:56,416
<i>[Stunning Attack with a Sword]</i>

567
00:29:01,640 --> 00:29:02,880
Mengnan,

568
00:29:02,880 --> 00:29:04,980
you've been too tense lately.

569
00:29:04,980 --> 00:29:06,160
Too strong will snap.

570
00:29:06,840 --> 00:29:07,880
Today, you're here

571
00:29:07,880 --> 00:29:09,640
to release all your stress.

572
00:29:12,760 --> 00:29:15,000
So that's why you brought me here.

573
00:29:15,880 --> 00:29:16,896
Exactly.

574
00:29:18,200 --> 00:29:19,320
There are three types of swords.

575
00:29:20,240 --> 00:29:21,360
This one is a broadsword.

576
00:29:21,360 --> 00:29:23,500
Its weight is the heaviest
among the three kinds.

577
00:29:23,500 --> 00:29:24,760
It's not quite suitable for girls.

578
00:29:26,600 --> 00:29:28,020
This one is a foil.

579
00:29:28,020 --> 00:29:30,900
Its rules are relatively complex.

580
00:29:30,900 --> 00:29:31,968
It's not really suitable for you.

581
00:29:32,480 --> 00:29:33,536
Really?

582
00:29:35,200 --> 00:29:36,400
This one is a rapier.

583
00:29:36,400 --> 00:29:38,720
Its weight is relatively lighter.

584
00:29:38,720 --> 00:29:40,720
It's especially suitable
for beginners like you.

585
00:29:42,960 --> 00:29:44,000
You try it.

586
00:29:52,360 --> 00:29:54,140
How about having a bout?

587
00:29:54,140 --> 00:29:55,440
Okay.

588
00:29:55,440 --> 00:29:56,544
Let's do it.

589
00:30:09,840 --> 00:30:11,520
I didn't expect that you have such talent.

590
00:30:17,080 --> 00:30:19,840
I didn't expect you have such luck
in addition to talent.

591
00:30:19,840 --> 00:30:20,896
Let's do it.

592
00:30:26,480 --> 00:30:28,040
Okay, that's good. Let's do it again.

593
00:30:37,200 --> 00:30:38,304
I'm going to get serious now.

594
00:31:06,440 --> 00:31:08,440
How are you? Are you okay?

595
00:31:17,920 --> 00:31:19,680
I didn't expect your sword techniques
to be so good.

596
00:31:20,840 --> 00:31:21,856
How long have you been practicing?

597
00:31:22,840 --> 00:31:24,720
Six years. I appreciate your guidance.

598
00:31:28,720 --> 00:31:29,720
I have learned a lot.

599
00:31:32,880 --> 00:31:33,888
Let's take a break.

600
00:32:06,200 --> 00:32:07,400
Are you hungry?

601
00:32:07,400 --> 00:32:09,280
These noodles with egg will take a while.

602
00:32:10,840 --> 00:32:13,400
Don't you smell something strange in the house?

603
00:32:14,320 --> 00:32:15,424
No, I don't.

604
00:32:27,920 --> 00:32:28,920
What is this?

605
00:32:28,920 --> 00:32:30,200
This is something I brought especially for you.

606
00:32:30,200 --> 00:32:32,160
It's our home-made green mango pickle.

607
00:32:32,160 --> 00:32:33,400
Throw it away.

608
00:32:33,400 --> 00:32:35,360
What are you doing?
You shouldn't throw it away.

609
00:32:35,360 --> 00:32:38,120
This is a good thing. My mom asked me
to bring this for you.

610
00:32:40,440 --> 00:32:42,320
Why don't you taste it first? Try it.

611
00:32:42,320 --> 00:32:43,980
No, I absolutely won't.

612
00:32:43,980 --> 00:32:46,160
Please don't bring it
so close to my nose, okay?

613
00:32:50,080 --> 00:32:51,720
You can feel free to insult me.

614
00:32:51,720 --> 00:32:53,120
But you cannot ignore

615
00:32:53,120 --> 00:32:54,880
my mom's kind intentions, right?

616
00:32:54,880 --> 00:32:57,400
Before I left, she asked me
to bring two cans for you

617
00:32:57,400 --> 00:32:59,020
to try.

618
00:32:59,020 --> 00:33:00,400
She prepared it herself.

619
00:33:01,360 --> 00:33:04,440
She just wanted you
to have a taste of our specialty.

620
00:33:04,440 --> 00:33:05,472
Try it out.

621
00:33:26,840 --> 00:33:28,240
How is it?

622
00:33:28,240 --> 00:33:29,520
It smells a bit off.

623
00:33:29,520 --> 00:33:31,000
But it tastes quite good
when you actually eat it.

624
00:33:32,760 --> 00:33:34,000
Don't worry.

625
00:33:34,000 --> 00:33:35,160
There's still more.

626
00:33:35,720 --> 00:33:37,360
Don't be embarrassed if you don't have enough.

627
00:33:37,360 --> 00:33:38,800
I can bring you more.

628
00:33:38,800 --> 00:33:39,800
There's another can here.

629
00:33:44,672 --> 00:33:45,680
What is that?

630
00:33:45,680 --> 00:33:47,360
This? Mold.

631
00:33:49,640 --> 00:33:51,520
These pickles need to be marinated
for a long time.

632
00:33:51,520 --> 00:33:52,800
Otherwise, they won't have a strong flavor.

633
00:33:52,800 --> 00:33:54,560
Finding mold is quite normal.

634
00:33:57,760 --> 00:33:58,960
Well…

635
00:33:58,960 --> 00:34:00,280
So delicious.

636
00:34:00,280 --> 00:34:01,760
Is it really that awful?

637
00:34:04,240 --> 00:34:05,248
So delicious.

638
00:34:27,120 --> 00:34:28,520
Tian Tian,

639
00:34:28,520 --> 00:34:30,280
- what did you put in here?
- What's wrong?

640
00:34:32,800 --> 00:34:34,400
Where did you put my mouthwash?

641
00:34:35,800 --> 00:34:37,900
This is mine…

642
00:34:37,900 --> 00:34:38,912
I…

643
00:34:40,239 --> 00:34:43,560
My bottle broke when I came this morning.

644
00:34:45,040 --> 00:34:46,639
Do you have any empty bottles?

645
00:34:54,239 --> 00:34:55,679
There's only a little bit left in this one.

646
00:34:55,679 --> 00:34:56,840
It should be okay if I pour it out.

647
00:34:57,600 --> 00:34:58,624
Just right.

648
00:35:01,680 --> 00:35:03,680
I forgot to tell you.

649
00:35:07,400 --> 00:35:08,720
I'm sorry.

650
00:35:18,320 --> 00:35:19,480
I'm all sweaty.

651
00:35:19,480 --> 00:35:20,600
I feel so comfortable today.

652
00:35:22,240 --> 00:35:23,420
Thank you just now.

653
00:35:23,420 --> 00:35:24,520
You didn't slap my face.

654
00:35:25,640 --> 00:35:26,760
I let you off the hook.

655
00:35:28,120 --> 00:35:30,200
Of course, you have to film tomorrow.

656
00:35:30,960 --> 00:35:32,640
It seems I was presumptuous.

657
00:35:33,560 --> 00:35:35,520
Aren't you men always like this,

658
00:35:35,520 --> 00:35:37,180
playing the teacher

659
00:35:37,180 --> 00:35:39,440
and thinking we women can't do anything?

660
00:35:42,360 --> 00:35:43,480
For this issue,

661
00:35:44,160 --> 00:35:45,320
I reserve my opinion.

662
00:35:54,640 --> 00:35:55,760
You listen to his music too?

663
00:35:56,720 --> 00:35:57,760
Do you listen to it too?

664
00:35:58,680 --> 00:36:00,680
I started listening a few years ago.

665
00:36:00,680 --> 00:36:03,100
This is one of my favorite singers.

666
00:36:03,100 --> 00:36:04,840
I have many of his records at home.

667
00:36:04,840 --> 00:36:06,280
If you have time, we can listen together.

668
00:36:10,400 --> 00:36:15,232
<i>♫ Through the darkness
and the fear in my heart ♫</i>

669
00:36:17,856 --> 00:36:22,176
<i>♫ If I could hear the whisper in the wind ♫</i>

670
00:36:24,416 --> 00:36:29,248
<i>♫ Perhaps it would surround me ♫</i>

671
00:36:31,872 --> 00:36:33,952
<i>♫ Because I am prepared ♫</i>

672
00:36:59,480 --> 00:37:00,512
What's wrong?

673
00:37:01,080 --> 00:37:02,420
Well,

674
00:37:02,420 --> 00:37:04,340
I poured out all the toner.

675
00:37:04,340 --> 00:37:06,160
I also cleaned your bottle.

676
00:37:06,160 --> 00:37:07,400
I noticed we ran out of mouthwash at home.

677
00:37:07,400 --> 00:37:09,480
So I bought one online,
it will arrive tomorrow.

678
00:37:12,200 --> 00:37:13,260
What else?

679
00:37:13,260 --> 00:37:16,200
I also cleaned up all my stuff on the floor.

680
00:37:17,360 --> 00:37:19,920
Are we not eating pickle in the future?

681
00:37:19,920 --> 00:37:20,960
Pickle…

682
00:37:21,472 --> 00:37:24,120
Try not to eat pickle.

683
00:37:25,920 --> 00:37:26,944
We won't eat it.

684
00:37:28,280 --> 00:37:30,140
All right, I forgive you.

685
00:37:30,140 --> 00:37:31,232
Wait a minute.

686
00:37:32,600 --> 00:37:34,100
There's one more thing.

687
00:37:34,100 --> 00:37:35,360
What is it?

688
00:37:35,360 --> 00:37:37,000
Now that you're not angry anymore,

689
00:37:37,560 --> 00:37:39,440
let's watch a movie together.

690
00:37:42,400 --> 00:37:43,488
Okay.

691
00:37:51,080 --> 00:37:52,360
No.

692
00:37:52,360 --> 00:37:53,840
If you want to watch a movie, just watch it.

693
00:37:53,840 --> 00:37:55,140
Why are you turning off the light?

694
00:37:55,140 --> 00:37:57,800
For a horror movie,
the atmosphere is very important.

695
00:38:06,800 --> 00:38:08,040
It's starting, it's starting.

696
00:38:08,040 --> 00:38:09,680
I know it's starting.

697
00:38:29,800 --> 00:38:32,120
I suddenly thought of

698
00:38:33,240 --> 00:38:34,440
a grand business plan.

699
00:38:34,440 --> 00:38:36,720
I feel that I must write it down.

700
00:38:36,720 --> 00:38:38,200
This will concern

701
00:38:38,200 --> 00:38:40,360
the life-and-death situation of my company.

702
00:38:41,840 --> 00:38:42,912
Don't.

703
00:38:43,680 --> 00:38:45,200
You were watching the movie just fine.

704
00:38:45,200 --> 00:38:46,720
What's with the sudden plan writing?

705
00:38:51,760 --> 00:38:53,560
Are you scared?

706
00:38:56,280 --> 00:38:57,900
Are you kidding me?

707
00:38:57,900 --> 00:38:59,340
How can I be scared?

708
00:38:59,340 --> 00:39:00,416
Just…

709
00:39:05,560 --> 00:39:06,640
Will I be scared?

710
00:39:09,040 --> 00:39:10,440
Just don't be scared.

711
00:39:14,640 --> 00:39:16,240
I can't, I'm scared.

712
00:39:25,600 --> 00:39:27,220
Did you see that?

713
00:39:27,220 --> 00:39:28,800
Yes, I saw it.

714
00:39:57,280 --> 00:39:58,600
Well, why are you always looking at me?

715
00:39:58,600 --> 00:40:00,120
Watch the movie, okay?

716
00:40:00,120 --> 00:40:02,720
I'm just checking if you're really watching.

717
00:40:02,720 --> 00:40:04,240
I've been watching all along.

718
00:40:04,240 --> 00:40:06,520
There's nothing to be scared of, it's all fake.

719
00:40:07,880 --> 00:40:09,360
I'm still scared.

720
00:40:12,920 --> 00:40:14,660
You frightened me to death.

721
00:40:14,660 --> 00:40:16,680
You scared me.

722
00:40:32,360 --> 00:40:33,408
Carlo.

723
00:40:51,080 --> 00:40:52,120
Gao Zhuo.

724
00:41:10,640 --> 00:41:11,680
You're awake.

725
00:41:12,256 --> 00:41:13,280
A pot of tea, please.

726
00:41:13,280 --> 00:41:14,360
Alright, please wait a moment.

727
00:41:18,160 --> 00:41:19,760
Did you not sleep well?

728
00:41:21,200 --> 00:41:22,272
Did not sleep much.

729
00:41:25,920 --> 00:41:27,680
Has Miss Tian moved in yet?

730
00:41:30,080 --> 00:41:32,400
Are you going to pick her up later?

731
00:41:32,400 --> 00:41:34,400
No need, I've recorded her fingerprint for her.

732
00:41:42,480 --> 00:41:44,080
Although the two of you have moved in together,

733
00:41:44,840 --> 00:41:46,160
I still hope

734
00:41:46,160 --> 00:41:48,160
that you can keep a certain distance.

735
00:41:48,160 --> 00:41:50,320
If you get too close,

736
00:41:50,320 --> 00:41:52,640
letting her know some things
she shouldn't know,

737
00:41:53,200 --> 00:41:54,880
I'm afraid it will be difficult
to deal with in the future.

738
00:41:56,720 --> 00:41:57,760
Okay, thank you.

739
00:42:00,560 --> 00:42:01,632
Have some tea.

740
00:42:27,168 --> 00:42:30,688
<i>♫ Your gaze is unwavering ♫</i>

741
00:42:32,704 --> 00:42:37,248
<i>♫ Only enough to accommodate me ♫</i>

742
00:42:38,464 --> 00:42:43,136
<i>♫ I have been melted by you countless times ♫</i>

743
00:42:44,096 --> 00:42:47,648
<i>♫ Yet I'm at a loss for what to do ♫</i>

744
00:42:49,600 --> 00:42:52,544
<i>♫ I can only hold on to you ♫</i>

745
00:42:54,624 --> 00:42:58,528
<i>♫ Now you are still with me ♫</i>

746
00:43:00,192 --> 00:43:04,448
<i>♫ Traveling through time together ♫</i>

747
00:43:06,304 --> 00:43:14,240
<i>♫ Someday, I'll be completely
forgotten by the world ♫</i>

748
00:43:14,240 --> 00:43:17,440
<i>♫ Leaving no trace ♫</i>

749
00:43:17,440 --> 00:43:21,472
<i>♫ Only you will still remember ♫</i>

750
00:43:23,232 --> 00:43:25,536
<i>♫ My appearance ♫</i>
